🚀Bobby Watson "Solo Architecture” LIVE Masterclass + Q&A! DETAILS: http://JazzHeaven.com/live
#bobbywatson #saxophone #jazzheaven
Bobby covered:
Solo Architecture
Rhythmic, Melodic & Linear Approaches to build & shape Your Solos

Enter Bobby:

The following short, thought-provoking phrases/quotes contain a lot of insight and were very influential to me.

My concept is based on these and other things that have been said to me by great musicians over the years.

And I have been able to use all of that to develop my own style & concept.

I will go in detail about these (and more) in our live masterclass.

* "Let the punishment fit the crime.” (Melodic Improvisation)

* "Somebody goofed, and Jazz was born.” (Melodic Embellishment)

* "It don't mean a thing if it ain't got that swing.” (Rhythmic Improvisation)

* "Take some, leave some." (Linear Improvisation)

* "The 4th quality of music.” (Phrasing)

* "Go high when it's time to go high.” (Building and Shaping your Solo)

Masterclass + Q&A + 1-on-1 HOT SEATS where YOU can be live on screen via webcam & get 1-on-1 Feedback from Bobby.

Details: http://JazzHeaven.com/live

Veteran Alto Saxophonist Alert!

​Bobby was the musical director for Art Blakey's Jazz Messengers for five years and played & recorded with the likes of Wynton Marsalis, Branford Marsalis, Max Roach, Joe Williams, Dianne Reeves, Lou Rawls & Betty Carter.

His renowned band Horizon recorded for the Blue Note and Columbia record labels.

He also composed a song for the soundtrack to the Robert De Niro movie "A Bronx Tale."

A skilled educator, Bobby taught at schools like William Paterson University and Manhattan School of Music and was a distinguished professor and the director of jazz studies at the University of Missouri - Kansas City Conservatory of Music while still managing a worldwide performing schedule.

Details: http://JazzHeaven.com/live
